<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-401-664  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 401 664.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Week  July 3 1989 v6 n26 p21(2)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Fox's new Mac database praised for its graphical report writer.andO;(Software Review) (Fox Software Inc.)andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Freedman, Beth.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Fox Software Inc. (products).andO;Product:   Apple Macintosh (Microcomputer) (computer programs)FoxBASE Plus-Mac 2.0 (Data base management system) (evaluation).andO;Topic:     Data base management systemsEvaluationReport Generators.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>By Beth FreedmanandM;As version 2.0 of Fox Software Inc.'s Macintosh database hit dealers' shelveslast week, early users of the software unanimously praised its report writerfor being easier to use.andM;FoxBase+/Mac 2.0 features a new report writer fashioned after the graphicaland iconic style of the Macintosh's MacDraw user interface.andP;  The earlierversion of FoxBase+/Mac incorporated a character-based report writerpatterned after those in FoxBase for the PC and dBASE III Plus.andM;The inclusion of a graphical interface and a toolbox of graphical objects,such as boxes and rectangles, puts the ability to build complex reports inthe hands of non-technical users who don't want to learn dBASE-likeprogramming, said Dave Fester, a senior analyst with the Space InformationSystems division of Martin Marietta Corp. in Lakewood, Colo., and a betatester of the new version.andM;&quot;FoxBase+/Mac 2.0 lets end users create custom reports in no time and withlittle effort, simply by placing objects anywhere on the page,&quot; Fester said.andM;The new report writer works in a similar way to FoxBase+/ Mac's screenpainter, bringing overall consistency to the package, said TerraleeParkinson, management-system analyst at Hughes Aircraft Co. in Long Beach,Calif.andP;  Another bonus is the new release's ability to show users an on-screenpreview of how their documents will appear after they are output to aprinter, she said.andM;Other improvements to FoxBase+/Mac 2.0 cited by users are a boost inperformance and the ability to access external functions.andM;&quot;FoxBase+/Mac 2.0 is noticeably faster, and it runs a little smoother,&quot; saidJon Olson, directory coordinator at Cellular Directory Corp., a Cary, N.C.,andO;company that markets phone books for the cellular-telephone industry.andP;  Olsonalso hailed the program's new ability to access external XFCN or XCMDfunctions written in Apple Computer Inc.'s HyperCard, C language or Pascal,which can come in handy for adding an auto-dialing function to anapplication, he  said.andM;FoxBase+/Mac 2.0 also incorporates a new, automatic label generator, a numberof new language enhancements and support for customized, hierarchical menus.andM;Available now, the software costs $495 for a single-user version and $695 fora multiuser version.andP;  Registered owners can upgrade to the single-userrelease for $75 and to the multiuser version for $95.andM;Fox Software, of Perrysburg, Ohio, can be reached at (419) 874-0162.andO;</TEXT></DOC>